# StoryCompiler

**A native macOS writing application for novel authors across all genres (fantasy, sci-fi, thrillers, romance, and more) with integrated worldbuilding management, entity tracking, relationship mapping, and a full Project Dashboard for world research and visualisation.**

---

## Vision

StoryCompiler treats a novel the way a compiler treats code. As the author writes prose, the application silently builds a structured knowledge graph of every entity in the world — characters, locations, factions, objects, events — and the relationships between them. By the final chapter, the author has a fully populated worldbuilding database built as a natural byproduct of the writing process itself, with zero separate data entry.

The app's flexible entity types, custom predicates, and visualization tools adapt seamlessly to any genre—whether mapping interstellar politics in sci-fi, suspect relationships in thrillers, or emotional arcs in romance.

The application has two primary modes:

**Writing Workspace** — the 6-zone editor where the author writes prose, tags entities, locks subjects, defines relationships, and captures scenes and dialogue.

**Project Dashboard** — the worldbuilding studio where the author plans, researches, visualises, and understands their world. Timeline, map, mind map, notes, and sheets all live here, all connected to the same entity database the workspace produces.

