## Core Concepts

### Entity Types

StoryCompiler ships with 10 built-in entity types as a starting template. They cover the most common worldbuilding categories across various novel genres.

| Symbol | Type | Shortcut | Definition |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@` | Character | `⌘⌥C` | A person or being |
| `#` | Location | `⌘⌥L` | A place |
| `&` | Faction | `⌘⌥F` | Any organised group |
| `$` | Heritage | `⌘⌥H` | Origin — ethnicity, species, nationality |
| `*` | Object | `⌘⌥O` | Any significant item |
| `~` | Event | `⌘⌥E` | Any significant occurrence |
| `?` | Language | `⌘⌥G` | Any communication system |
| `+` | Role | `⌘⌥R` | Any title, rank, or occupation |
| `!` | Concept | `⌘⌥I` | Any system, rule, or force |
| `%` | Theme | `⌘⌥M` | Narrative themes and motifs |

These 10 types are a **seed template**, not a fixed list. The writer can add any number of custom types to match their specific world — `Spice`, `Weave`, `Sigil`, `Prophecy`, anything.

---

### Custom Entity Types

Every world is different. The 10 built-in types will not cover every book ever written. A writer working on *Dune* needs `Spice`. A writer working on *Wheel of Time* needs `Weave`. A writer working on *Game of Thrones* needs `Sigil`. A thriller writer needs `Suspect`; a romance author needs `Trope`; a sci-fi creator needs `Technology`.

**Manage Entity Types** is accessible from Settings. It shows the full type table — built-ins and custom — and lets the writer add, edit, or remove types freely.

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ Entity Types                                      + New Type     │
├────────┬─────────────┬───────────┬───────────────────────────────┤
│ Symbol │ Name        │ Shortcut  │ Definition                    │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Built-in · 10 types                                             │
│   @    Character     ⌘⌥C        A person or being    [built-in] │
│   #    Location      ⌘⌥L        A place              [built-in] │
│   ...                                                            │
├──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  Custom · 2 types                                                │
│   ✦    Spice         ⌘⌥S        Naturally occurring  ✏️  🗑️    │
│                                  substance (Arrakis)             │
│   ≋    Weave         ⌘⌥W        A pattern in the One ✏️  🗑️    │
│                                  Power                           │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Rules:**
- Built-in types can be edited but not deleted
- Custom types are fully editable and deletable
- Each type needs a unique name, symbol, keyboard shortcut key, colour, and definition
- Shortcut conflicts are detected and blocked at save time
- Custom types participate in everything — inline tagging, Subject Lock, Define Relationship, predicate autocomplete — identically to built-in types

