### Inline Tagging

While writing, the author tags selected words directly in the prose using keyboard shortcuts. Tagged words render as coloured inline spans — visually distinct but non-intrusive.

**Shortcut:** `⌘⌥` + the type's assigned key

```
Built-in types:
⌘⌥C  →  tag as Character    (blue)
⌘⌥L  →  tag as Location     (green)
⌘⌥F  →  tag as Faction      (orange)
⌘⌥H  →  tag as Heritage     (red)
⌘⌥O  →  tag as Object       (dark red)
⌘⌥E  →  tag as Event        (cyan)
⌘⌥G  →  tag as Language     (light blue)
⌘⌥R  →  tag as Role         (amber)
⌘⌥I  →  tag as Concept      (green/light)
⌘⌥M  →  tag as Theme        (brown)

Custom types (examples):
⌘⌥S  →  tag as Spice        (writer-chosen colour)
⌘⌥W  →  tag as Weave        (writer-chosen colour)
```

The underlying file stores raw syntax tokens. The editor deserialises them into coloured spans on load and reserialises on save — the round-trip is invisible to the writer.

> ⚠️ **Implementation status:** Inline tagging shortcuts are designed and specified but not yet wired up. Currently entities are created via the syntax parser on chapter save. TaggedEditorView (NSTextView-based) is the next major milestone.

